President Barack Obama will award Captain Florent A. Groberg the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions during combat operations in Afghanistan in 2012. Captain Groberg will be the tenth living recipient to receive the Medal of Honor for actions in Afghanistan. He will join the President at the White House for a ceremony to commemorate his selfless service. Captain Groberg was born in France and became a naturalized U.S. citizen in 2001. He served in the Army as an Infantry Officer and was deployed to Afghanistan multiple times. In August 2012, he was injured during combat and spent his recovery at Walter Reed National Military Medical Center. Captain Groberg's awards and decorations include the Bronze Star Medal, Purple Heart, and Meritorious Service Medal, among others. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who display gallantry above and beyond the call of duty.